WEBVTT

00:00:14.464 --> 00:00:15.665 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Anger,

00:00:22.706 --> 00:00:25.041 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
hurtful words,

00:00:37.654 --> 00:00:40.490 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
devastating effects

00:00:45.195 --> 00:00:47.630 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—the Bible says:

00:00:47.630 --> 00:00:51.835 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“A mild answer turns away rage,

00:00:51.835 --> 00:00:55.905 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but a harsh word stirs up anger.”

00:00:57.974 --> 00:01:00.877 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The way out of a crisis is only found

00:01:00.877 --> 00:01:04.781 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by learning to speak openly with one another

00:01:07.383 --> 00:01:10.620 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in a mild, gentle way.

00:01:14.324 --> 00:01:17.927 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It takes time and patience.

00:01:19.763 --> 00:01:21.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Honestly apologizing

00:01:21.865 --> 00:01:24.768 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
also helps to build bridges.

00:01:28.404 --> 00:01:32.108 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The insight of a man
certainly slows down his anger,”

00:01:32.108 --> 00:01:34.110 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
says the Bible.

00:01:35.545 --> 00:01:38.681 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Insight means understanding

00:01:40.617 --> 00:01:43.853 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—to have empathy for my partner.

00:01:44.888 --> 00:01:48.124 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How can I understand
the feelings behind their reaction?

00:01:49.692 --> 00:01:52.495 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How were my words understood?

00:01:53.797 --> 00:01:58.601 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Speaking so as not to hurt
one another’s feelings will help.

00:02:02.172 --> 00:02:05.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When was everything OK between us?

00:02:09.512 --> 00:02:12.382 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What were the things that made us happy?

00:02:15.218 --> 00:02:17.954 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Can we revive this love again?

00:02:25.728 --> 00:02:28.298 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
go in a new direction?

